Scaling Laws for Pre-training Agents and World Models","ecture using a transformer with 1M parameters. Observe from Figure 4 that BC-Token receives dz+da= 556 inputs for every action ˆatit predicts, while BC-CNN receives just one input for every action predicted. Hence, BC-Token uses around 556 times more compute in its action prediction ( 556×2×1M≈1×109FLOPs) than BC-CNN ( 1×2×1M≈2×106FLOPs). This means that even with the same number of parameters, BC-Token can learn a far more expressive function than BC-CNN. Hence, BC-Token requires far more tokens to match this expressivity, and training curves for a given model size plateau much later. 5.3. Q3: WM-"
